sec.p:
I see these as the goals of future higher education, not only for Chinese but also for all the institutions of higher education around the world. Another one of the Four Books, The Doctrine of the Mean (中庸), is also a fundamental guide for Chinese university education. The basic three principles in The Doctrine of the Mean are these:


What Heaven has conferred is called Nature (天命之謂性);

Accordance with nature is called Tao (率性之謂道);

The cultivation of Tao is called Education (修道之謂教).9
